hannels are pruned.\n\n### Short version\n\n- **Magnitude pruning**: prune small weights.\n- **Saliency/gradient/“cogalent” pruning**: prune weights or groups estimated to matter least.\n- **Structured pruning**: prune whole components like channels, heads, or layers.\n\nSo “cogalent pruning” would differ from structured pruning in that one is likely a **scoring rule**, while structured pruning is a **pruning granularity**.",
